      "content": "i mean i get the idea of \"completing the picture\" but it feels like a lot of people are saying that instead of just teaching facts, schools are now basically teaching kids what to think about things like systemic issues. do you think these changes are actually helping kids learn better, or is it just making schools more partisan?",
